SIMPLE: snort
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Snort
<hw>Snort</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Snorted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Snorting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>snorten</ets>; akin to
<ets>snoren</ets>. <ets>See</ets> <er>Snore</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To force the air with violence through the nose, so as to make a
noise, as do high-spirited horsed in prancing and play.</def>
<rj><au>Fairfax.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To snore.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>snorting</xex> citizens.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To laugh out loudly.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Snort
<hw>Snort</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of snorting; the sound
produced in snorting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snort</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Snort
<hw>Snort</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To expel through the nostrils with
a snort; to utter with a snort.</def> <rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Snorter</ent>⟦br⟧
